oc:kn_05884d77 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When recommending email count and cadence if user hasn't specified" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the 8 sequence type templates as starting frameworks (Onboarding: 5-7 emails/14-21 days, Lead Nurture: 4-6 emails/3-4 weeks, Re-engagement: 3-4 emails/10-14 days, Win-back: 3-5 emails/30 days, Product Launch: 4-6 emails/2-3 weeks, Event Follow-up: 3-4 emails/7-10 days, Upgrade/Upsell: 3-5 emails/2-3 weeks, Educational Drip: 5-8 emails/4-6 weeks)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These frameworks encode proven timing patterns for each lifecycle stage; deviating without reason risks under- or over-messaging." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_07bdb18b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When finalizing the sequence output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Include 2-3 A/B test suggestions per sequence (subject lines, CTA text, send time, email length) with what to test, how to split, and how to measure the winner." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A/B testing is essential for optimizing sequence performance over time; providing specific test recommendations ensures the user has an actionable optimization roadmap." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_141b1327 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing individual emails within a sequence" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each email must have exactly one primary CTA; secondary CTAs are only appropriate at certain sequence stages. Subject lines should stay under 50 characters. Preview text should be 40-90 characters that complements (not repeats) the subject line." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Multiple competing CTAs dilute click-through; subject line length affects mobile truncation; preview text that repeats the subject line wastes the secondary attention line." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4ff2d9d2 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When starting any email sequence design" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Define the overall sequence architecture (narrative arc, journey mapping, escalation logic, success definition) before drafting any individual emails." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Starting with individual emails without a strategic framework leads to disjointed sequences that lack coherent progression toward a conversion goal." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_953ecb4c a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining sequence logic and flow control" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Define suppression rules: do not send if the recipient is already in another active sequence, has unsubscribed from marketing, or has contacted support in the last 48 hours." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Suppression rules prevent overlapping messaging, respect unsubscribe preferences, and avoid tone-deaf marketing sends to users with active support issues." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_af125f44 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building sequence flow logic" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not skip defining exit conditions and re-entry rules. Every sequence must specify what 'conversion' means and whether/how recipients can re-enter." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing exit conditions lead to recipients continuing to receive irrelevant emails after converting; missing re-entry rules create gaps for recurring lifecycle scenarios." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

